messages.content: What is the purpose of the ComfyUI_Fooocus_KSampler custom node?
The ComfyUI_Fooocus_KSampler custom node incorporates the functionality of Fooocus/modules into ComfyUI, exchanging the TAESD previewer with the standard one in core.py.
What is the source of the ComfyUI_Fooocus_KSampler custom node?
The ComfyUI_Fooocus_KSampler custom node comes directly from Fooocus, which is available on GitHub at https://github.com/lllyasviel/Fooocus.
Which file was modified in the Fooocus/modules to create the ComfyUI_Fooocus_KSampler custom node?
The core.py file in the Fooocus/modules was modified to exchange the TAESD previewer with the standard one to create the ComfyUI_Fooocus_KSampler custom node.
What was changed in the core.py file to create the ComfyUI_Fooocus_KSampler custom node?
In the core.py file, the TAESD previewer was exchanged with the standard one to create the ComfyUI_Fooocus_KSampler custom node.
Is the ComfyUI_Fooocus_KSampler custom node an exact copy of Fooocus/modules?
No, the ComfyUI_Fooocus_KSampler custom node is not an exact copy of Fooocus/modules. It incorporates the functionality of Fooocus/modules but with a modification in the core.py file.
Does the ComfyUI_Fooocus_KSampler custom node use the TAESD previewer?
No, the ComfyUI_Fooocus_KSampler custom node does not use the TAESD previewer. It uses the standard previewer in the core.py file instead.
What is the main difference between the ComfyUI_Fooocus_KSampler custom node and the original Fooocus/modules?

The main difference between the ComfyUI_Fooocus_KSampler custom node and the original Fooocus/modules is that the custom node uses the standard previewer instead of the TAESD previewer in the core.py file.
